<div><div><h2>Venezuela and Panama To Launch Joint Panama Papers Investigation</h2></div><div>the joint investigation will be the &#8220;first of its kind&#8221; and venezuela&#8217;s attorney general has hinted at a long list of suspects. the attorney general of venezuela has announced an unprecedented joint investigation with their panamanian counterparts to probe individuals suspected of wrongdoing after their names surfaced in the panama papers. luisa ortega d\xc3\xadaz venezuela\xe2\x80\x99s attorney general since 2007 shared news of the partnership in a <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch v=hudlgd_dlqu">television interview</a> on sunday. \xe2\x80\x9ci sent a letter to the attorney general of panama and we created a joint task force of panamanian and venezuelan prosecutors \xe2\x80\x93 the first of its kind \xe2\x80\x93 to investigate these cases\xe2\x80\x9d venezuela\xe2\x80\x99s top prosecutor told television network televen. ortega hinted that her office\xe2\x80\x99s inquiry had produced a long list of suspects one of which has already been taken into custody. the panama papers revelations led to the <a href="http://www.lapatilla.com/site/2016/06/04/fiscalia-acusa-a-empresario-josmel-velasquez-figueroa-por-caso-de-papeles-de-panama/">indictment of venezuelan businessman josmel vel\xc3\xa1squez</a> and his mother on charges of money laundering and participation in a criminal conspiracy. according to the prosecutor\xe2\x80\x99s office both were taken into custody last april \xe2\x80\x9cafter searches at a string of vel\xc3\xa1squez-figueroa family properties where luxury cars high powered motorcycles empty rolex watch cases precious stones and diamond certificates were seized.\xe2\x80\x9d the pair were attempting to leave the country when they were apprehended at a private airport near caracas. an investigation by <a href="http://panamapapersvenezuela.com/">icij\xe2\x80\x99s venezuelan partners</a> also implicated <a href="http://panamapapersvenezuela.com/adrian-velasquez/">vel\xc3\xa1squez\xe2\x80\x99s brother adri\xc3\xa1n</a>. a retired army captain adri\xc3\xa1n vel\xc3\xa1squez  was former venezuelan president hugo ch\xc3\xa1vez&#39;s chief bodyguard. his wife claudia d\xc3\xadaz who also appears in the documents was ch\xc3\xa1vez\xe2\x80\x99s personal nurse and managed a multimillion-dollar development fund as national treasurer. leaked documents from mossack fonseca the panamanian law firm at the center of the panama papers  investigation showed that adri\xc3\xa1n vel\xc3\xa1squez and d\xc3\xadaz hired the firm to <a href="http://www.univision.com/noticias/papeles-de-panama/un-matrimonio-cercano-a-chavez-termino-con-empresas-en-paraisos-fiscales-y-cuenta-en-suiza">set up companies</a> in the seychelles switzerland and panama icij\xe2\x80\x99s partners reported. other documents from the leak have shown that the ch\xc3\xa1vez government used mossack fonseca\xe2\x80\x99s services in 2007 to <a href="http://panamapapersvenezuela.com/el-gobierno-de-chavez-tambien-paso-por-mossack-fonseca/">set up veniran</a> a joint petrochemical venture between the state oil companies of venezuela and iran. according to internal correspondence uncovered by icij\xe2\x80\x99s venezuelan partners mossack fonseca executives reportedly opted to incorporate veniran in the british virgin islands instead of panama in order to avoid u.n. sanctions imposed on iran for its nuclear program. meanwhile argentina\xe2\x80\x99s attorney general has <a href="http://www.noticiasargentinas.com.ar/nuevosite/53680-grindetti-imputado-por-los-panama-papers.html">indicted n\xc3\xa9stor grindetti</a> the mayor of the industrial city of l\xc3\xa1nus for his <a href="https://panamapapers.icij.org/the_power_players/">involvement in an offshore company</a> brought to light by the panama papers. grindetti is a close ally of argentinian president mauricio macri whose name has also come up in the mossack fonseca documents. back in april grindetti <a href="http://www.clarin.com/politica/grindetti-rompio-silencio-panama-papers_0_1554444986.html">told argentine newspaper clar\xc3\xadn</a> that \xe2\x80\x9cthere [wasn\xe2\x80\x99t] any kind of controversial matter\xe2\x80\x9d and that \xe2\x80\x9cthe company [he had been connected to] has never had any kind of activity which is why it had not been declared.\xe2\x80\x9d almost three months after they were first published the panama papers continue to impact the world of offshore secrecy and how it is regulated. new zealand was the latest country to announce it would <a href="http://www.radionz.co.nz/news/political/307382/nz-foreign-trust-rules-inadequate-inquiry">introduce tighter restrictions on foreign trusts</a> after the author of a review commissioned by the government described current transparency requirements as \xe2\x80\x9clight-handed.\xe2\x80\x9d prime minister john key said  most of the report\xe2\x80\x99s recommendations were likely  be adopted.</div></div>